<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="303" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d303">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/8–845: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-10T17:00:00-04:00">September
                                    10, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1988. Deptels 1710, July 31 and 1818, Aug. 13.<note n="78" xml:id="d303fn78">See footnote 53, <ref target="#pg_331">p.
                                    331</ref>, and footnote 64, <ref target="#pg_337">p. 337</ref>,
                                respectively.</note> Please inform FonOff that Dept has now received
                            replies from French and Brit Govts agreeing to participate in appointing
                            proposed commission and that Dept will appreciate an early expression of
                            Soviet views in matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>